.TH nvmetest 1M
.SH NAME
nvmetest \- NVMe device testing utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
\fBnvmetest\fR [\fIOPTION\fR]
\fBnvmetest\fR [\fI-h\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I nvmetest
is a utility for testing NVMe devices through the IRIX SCSI translation
layer. It performs various diagnostic and performance tests on NVMe
controllers.
.PP
The utility auto-detects the NVMe controller by scanning
/hw/scsi_ctlr/0-15 and identifying devices with "NVMe" vendor ID.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h
Print a usage message on standard output and exit successfully.
.TP
.B \-d \fIPATH
\fRSpecify device path (default: auto-detect).
.TP
.B \-x
Enable extended debug output. Shows controller status by querying VPD
page 0xC0.
.TP
.B \-i
Test INQUIRY command. Displays vendor, product, and revision information.
.TP
.B \-c
Test READ CAPACITY command. Shows maximum LBA, block size, and total
capacity.
.TP
.B \-r \fILBA
\fRRead single block at specified LBA.
.TP
.B \-s \fILBA COUNT
\fRRead COUNT blocks starting at LBA.
.TP
.B \-W \fILBA
\fRWrite single block at specified LBA.
.TP
.B \-S \fILBA COUNT
\fRWrite COUNT blocks starting at LBA.
.TP
.B \-w \fILBA
\fRWrite/Read test at specified LBA.
.TP
.B \-R \fIITERATIONS
\fRRandom write/read stress test (default: 100 iterations).
.TP
.B \-a
Run all basic tests.
